35:09.474 --> 35:11.843 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
countries in the rest of Europe
and perhaps
beyond?

35:11.876 --> 35:16.081 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LARS LOKKE RASMUSSEN, Danish
Prime Minister:
I think it's pretty obvious that
we are in

35:16.114 --> 35:22.754 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
a situation, if the European
Union can't protect
the external borders, you will
see more and

35:22.787 --> 35:31.596 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
more countries which will be
forced into introducing
temporary internal border
control.

35:31.629 --> 35:38.970 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
This is something we need to
take very seriously,
because it will have a negative
impact on

35:39.004 --> 35:47.278 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
