of the freedom
of movement. This is not a happy
moment at

35:47.312 --> 35:54.386 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
all. We have invested billions
in infrastructure
between Sweden and Denmark. We
have invested

35:54.419 --> 36:01.426 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
millions in international
branding of the
greater Copenhagen region. So,
this is a step

36:01.459 --> 36:03.261 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
backwards.

36:03.294 --> 36:07.132 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
MALCOLM BRABANT: Trine
Christensen, a senior
official at the human rights
group Amnesty

36:07.165 --> 36:11.503 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
International, is concerned that
other nations
along the refugee trail back to
Greece will

36:11.536 --> 36:16.941 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
now follow suit at a time when
migrants who
aren't from Syria, Iraq and
Afghanistan are

36:16.975 --> 36:18.676 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
stranded.

36:18.710 --> 36:22.047 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
TRINE CHRISTENSEN, Amnesty
International:
What we're seeing today is that
Sweden is

36:22.080 --> 36:27.685 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
desperately trying to get the
rest of Europe
to actually face up to its
responsibilities.

36:27.719 --> 36:34.092 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
If there is a European response
to this crisis,
there can be a solution. There
can be at least

36:34.125 --> 36:41.466 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
a way of distributing the
burdens and to help
people who are in desperate need
of protection.

36:41.499 --> 36:46.805 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: Christensen is
particularly
worried about the long-term
impact on Turkey,

36:46.838 --> 36:51.743 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Lebanon and Jordan, which have
taken in many
more refugees than the one
million or so who

36:51.776 --> 36:53.711 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
have entered Europe in the past
year.

36:53.745 --> 36:58.450 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
TRINE CHRISTENSEN: If we
continue to see what
is happening today, and that is
the majority

36:58.483 --> 37:04.389 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of countries trying to shirk
that responsibility,
trying to avoid helping, then we
will see

37:04.422 --> 37:11.162 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
a buildup of more and more
problems and more
and more refugees. And the
pressure on the

37:11.196 --> 37:15.934 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
local areas, on the neighboring
countries,
which they are not able to bear
in any way,

37:15.967 --> 37:21.706 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
shape or form. As that happens,
and those
countries start to implode,
that's when we

37:21.739 --> 37:26.111 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
will see a refugee problem that
will make
what we have today look like
nothing at all.

37:26.144 --> 37:30.849 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: But the most
pressing concern
for Michael Randropp is an
economic one. He

37:30.882 --> 37:36.221 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
represents 15,000 people who
live and work
in the cross-border region and
commute between

37:36.254 --> 37:40.859 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Denmark and Sweden. Their lives
have suddenly
become more complex and
disruptive.

37:40.892 --> 37:44.028 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MICHAEL RANDROPP, Government
Official: Some
of the passengers say that this
is a new Iron

37:44.062 --> 37:47.799 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Curtain. And other passengers
say that this
is a new Berlin Wall.

37:47.832 --> 37:53.605 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: For the past 20
years, businessman
Ture Ertmann has lived in
Sweden, where homes

37:53.638 --> 37:59.744 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and cars are cheaper, and worked
in Copenhagen.
But he's now contemplating
moving to Denmark.

37:59.777 --> 38:11.556 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MAN: Gentlemen, next stop, first
stop in Sweden.
In Sweden, we have border
control, so please

38:11.589 --> 38:13.358 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
have your passports or other
identification
cards ready.

38:13.391 --> 38:15.660 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
TURE ERTMANN, Businessman: The
whole idea
of the Schengen is that we have
external border

38:15.693 --> 38:20.131 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
controls. And now, suddenly,
that seems to
be breaking down. And each
country is raising

38:20.165 --> 38:26.638 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the inner borders. So, suddenly,
the whole
European community, the whole
cooperation

38:26.671 --> 38:31.509 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
across borders seems to be
challenged a lot.
So, that's -- I think that's
worrisome.

38:31.543 --> 38:36.447 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: The impact of
the changes
is also being felt north of
Copenhagen on

38:36.481 --> 38:41.519 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the main ferry route lining
Denmark and Sweden,
which is in competition with the
bridge. The

38:41.553 --> 38:46.090 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ferry company fears the cost of
implementing
the new measures will cost at
least $3 million

38:46.124 --> 38:47.926 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
a year.

38:47.959 --> 38:53.064 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Chief executive Henrik Rorbaek
has complained
to the European Union about
Sweden's action

38:53.097 --> 38:55.066 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and wants Stockholm to pay
compensation.

38:55.099 --> 38:59.270 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HENRIK RORBAEK, Chief Executive:
It means
like, for example, if you're in
New York,

38:59.304 --> 39:05.577 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
wants to pass the Brooklyn
Bridge, then you
have to show an I.D. I'm quite
sure that every

39:05.610 --> 39:07.512 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
American would consider that as
a mess.

39:07.545 --> 39:10.148 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: It's another
nail in Schengen's
coffin.

39:10.181 --> 39:16.854 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LARS LOKKE RASMUSSEN: Hopefully
not. What
we need now is European leaders
who should

39:16.888 --> 39:22.994 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
respond to this. We have been
pushing and
pushing for a European solution.
So, this

39:23.027 --> 39:31.836 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
is a clear signal that your
Europe now needs
to take decisions which can
protect the external

39:31.869 --> 39:33.705 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
borders.

39:33.738 --> 39:36.341 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: Denmark's
actions have been
greeted with disappointment in
Germany, which,

39:36.374 --> 39:40.511 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
along with Sweden, has welcomed
most refugees
during this crisis.

39:40.545 --> 39:44.849 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The German Foreign Ministry
spokesman described
freedom of movement as the
European Union's

39:44.882 --> 39:49.153 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
greatest achievement, but he
warned that the
Schengen area was in danger. He
said it was

39:49.187 --> 39:53.625 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
crucial that common solutions
were found to
the migrant flow.

39:53.658 --> 39:59.564 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But throughout this crisis,
national interest
has taken priority over European
unity. Today's

39:59.597 --> 40:01.899 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
developments reinforce that
trend.

40:01.933 --> 40:08.373 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
For the "PBS NewsHour," I'm
Malcolm Brabant
in Copenhagen.

40:08.406 --> 40:20.285 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: For thousands of
young veterans
in America, putting the wars in
Afghanistan

40:20.318 --> 40:26.391 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and Iraq behind them remains a
constant challenge.
For some, starting a family is
an important

40:26.424 --> 40:28.026 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
part of the healing process.

40:28.059 --> 40:33.298 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But, as the "NewsHour"'s William
Brangham
reports, even that can be a
struggle.

40:33.331 --> 40:38.903 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: All newlyweds
face challenges,
but Jason and Rachel Hallett
have more challenges

40:38.936 --> 40:45.376 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
than most. Jason is a triple
amputee. Back
in 2010, at age 19, this young
Marine lost

40:45.410 --> 40:49.514 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
two legs and an arm when he
stepped on an
IED while on patrol in
Afghanistan.

40:49.547 --> 40:53.217 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CPL. JASON HALLETT (RET.), U.S.
Marine Corps:
When 9/11 and everything
happened, I was -- I

40:53.251 --> 40:57.155 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
had a little bit of interest to
join the military.
But, as soon as that happened,
it just became

40:57.188 --> 41:00.525 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
-- everything was circling
around me joining
the military.

41:00.558 --> 41:05.129 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: After his
injury, barely
clinging to life, and riddled
with infections,

41:05.163 --> 41:10.234 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Jason was cared for at U.S.
military facilities
in Germany, Maryland and
California.

41:10.268 --> 41:13.838 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He hadn't been in touch with
Rachel since
they dated back in eighth grade.
But, in the

41:13.871 --> 41:15.640 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
hospital, he found her again on
Facebook.

41:15.673 --> 41:19.210 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
RACHEL HALLETT, Wife of Jason
Hallett: He
sends me this friend request a
couple years

41:19.243 --> 41:26.651 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
after I had kind of given up.
And when I saw
what had happened, I just
started crying.

41:26.684 --> 41:33.257 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He hadn't posted, like, what
happened. But
he had, like -- his picture
obviously was

41:33.291 --> 41:38.262 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
different than last time I
remembered him,
and said that he worked for the
Marine Corps,

41:38.296 --> 41:40.198 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
so I kind of put two pieces
together.

41:40.231 --> 41:49.107 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Facebook led
to phone calls,
which led to a visit, and then a
wedding day.

41:49.140 --> 41:55.747 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They now live in Windsor,
Colorado. Jason's
studying to be a certified
financial planner.

41:55.780 --> 42:00.718 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Rachel baby-sits to make extra
money, but
her full-time job now really is
caring for

42:00.752 --> 42:04.489 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Jason, and she gets a small
stipend from the
VA for that work.

42:04.522 --> 42:09.060 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
What the Halletts want most is
to start a
family. But there's a problem.

42:09.093 --> 42:12.730 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
RACHEL HALLETT: We had just kind
of been told
that it would probably be a
problem because

42:12.764 --> 42:19.670 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of some of his injuries and
where his shrapnel
is. There's tons of shrapnel
everywhere throughout

42:19.704 --> 42:20.638 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
his body.

42:20.671 --> 42:22.407 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Still in your
body today?

42:22.440 --> 42:25.076 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CPL. JASON HALLETT: Yes. So,
basically, one
of the pieces had actually
connected itself

42:25.109 --> 42:28.980 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to one of my testicles. And so I
now have
to take testosterone injections
basically

42:29.013 --> 42:34.485 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to get me back to normal. And
with that, one
of the side effects is, it
basically kills

42:34.519 --> 42:36.354 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the sperm off.

42:36.387 --> 42:41.192 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: In order to
conceive a child,
the Halletts have to go through
lengthy in

42:41.225 --> 42:46.264 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
vitro fertilization treatments.
In vitro is
an expensive process. It
typically costs about

42:46.297 --> 42:53.938 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
$12,000 to $13,000 per try, and
the first
try often doesn't work, nor does
the second.

42:53.971 --> 42:59.177 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So the bills can stack up. But,
unlike all
the other medical treatment
related to Jason's

42:59.210 --> 43:04.148 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
injuries, the VA doesn't cover
IVF treatment
for wounded vets, and so the
young couple

43:04.182 --> 43:06.818 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
are paying for this themselves.

43:06.851 --> 43:11.122 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Congress passed a law in 1992
that led to
the Veterans Administration
banning coverage

43:11.155 --> 43:16.627 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
